    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 is a purist\u2019s specification, featuring the M96 3.4L flat-six mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis has been enhanced with Bilstein B8 dampers and M030-spec anti-roll bars, optimizing the MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension for superior lateral grip. Crucial preventative maintenance is documented, including a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The naturally aspirated power delivery is linear and tractable, pulling hard to the 7,200 RPM redline through a factory-optioned limited-slip differential. Braking performance remains sharp via four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers. This is a mechanically sound, driver-focused example with a clean bore-scope report and excellent compression across all cylinders.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Clean title. Regular maintenance performed. No major damage. Reliable runner.",
      "price": 29500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
